<TITLE>im2int32</TITLE>
<TYPE>SIVP Toolbox</TYPE>
<DATE>April, 2006</DATE>
<SHORT_DESCRIPTION name="im2int32">Convert image to 32-bit signed integers</SHORT_DESCRIPTION>
<CALLING_SEQUENCE>
   <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>im2 = im2int32(im)</CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
</CALLING_SEQUENCE>
<PARAM>
<PARAM_INDENT>
   <PARAM_ITEM>
   <PARAM_NAME>im</PARAM_NAME>
   <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
     An matrix/image, which can be ANY image supported by SIVP.
   </PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
   </PARAM_ITEM>
   <PARAM_ITEM>
   <PARAM_NAME>im2</PARAM_NAME>
   <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
     Output image, a 32-bit signed integer matrix.
   </PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
   </PARAM_ITEM>
</PARAM_INDENT>
</PARAM>
<DESCRIPTION>
<P>
<TT>im2int32</TT> convert intensity or RGB images to 32-bit signed integers.
If the input is of class <TT>int32</TT>, the output image is identical to it. 
Otherwise, <TT>im2int32</TT> rescales or offsets the data, and returns the equivalent image of class <TT>int32</TT>.
</P>
</DESCRIPTION>

